title: Landspace launches third methane Zhuque-2, targets 2025 launch of new stainless steel rocket
summary: Chinese launch startup Landspace successfully sent satellites into orbit for the first time Friday and revealed details of a new stainless steel rocket.

title: Gigantic Coronal Hole 60 Earths Wide Aims Radiation Directly at Earth
summary: An enormous dark hole has appeared on the surface of the sun, spewing powerful streams of unusually fast radiation, identified as solar wind, directly toward Earth.

title: Egypt Joins China ILRS Lunar Base Program
summary: Egypt is the latest country to sign a cooperation aggrement for China's International Lunar Research Station (ILRS).

title: Three satellites presumed lost in Transporter deployment malfunction
summary: Three satellites on a SpaceX Transporter rideshare launch in November failed to deploy, including one from a company that previously stated its satellite was in orbit and operating.

title: US Space Force Activates Europe and Africa Components
summary: USSPACEFOR-EURAF is now the newest service component under EUCOM and AFRICOM, joining the ranks of U.S. Indo-Pacific Command and U.S. Central Command in establishing a dedicated space component.

title: Ghana Warns Against Unauthorized Starlink Use
summary: Ghana has become the latest African nation to caution its citizens against using Starlink services before proper licensing is granted by the National Communications Authority.

title: Blue Origin New Shepard VR Experience Lands At NASA KSC Visitor Complex
summary: An immersive virtual reality experience inside a replica of Blue Origin’s New Shepard has landed at NASA Kennedy Space Centers Visitor Complex!

title: U.S. Space Force activates new unit to support operations in Europe and Africa
summary: The U.S. Space Force on Dec. 8 officially activated its first component dedicated to both Europe and Africa.

title: Ghana warns against illegal Starlink services
summary: Ghana is the latest country in Africa to warn against using Starlink before it issues licenses for SpaceX’s satellite broadband service.

title: Experts raise concerns about U.S. commitment to GPS modernization
summary: Members of a key advisory board questioned the U.S. military's commitment to deliver enhancements to the Global Positioning System, arguing that the network is at risk of falling behind other satellite navigation systems built by Europe and China.
